sys_hub_flow.description:
Retrieves entire data or updates made after the last refresh, for the selected entities.

  • Set 'Retrieve All Data' to 'True' to retrieve entire data of the selected entities.
  • If 'Retrieve All Data' is set to 'False', only the updates made after the last refresh are retrieved.
  • If data hasn’t been retrieved for the selected entity, entire data is retrieved irrespective of the value provided for 'Retrieve All Data'.

Inputs:

  • Department - Retrieves the department data from Workday.
  • Location - Retrieves the location data from Workday.
  • Job Profile - Retrieves the job profile data from Workday.
  • Worker Profile - Retrieves the worker profile data from Workday.
  • Effective Worker Profile - Retrieves the Effective Worker Profiles data from Workday.
  • Future Worker Profile - Retrieves the Future Worker Profiles data from Workday.
  • Employment Data - Retrieves the Employment data from Workday.
  • Retrieve All Data - Retrieves entire data for the selected entities.

To use this subflow, Workday Spoke must be installed and corresponding Workday Connection and Credential must be created.

sys_hub_flow_snapshot.description:
Retrieves entire data or updates made after the last refresh, for the selected entities.

  • Set 'Retrieve All Data' to 'True' to retrieve entire data of the selected entities.
  • If 'Retrieve All Data' is set to 'False', only the updates made after the last refresh are retrieved.
  • If data hasn’t been retrieved for the selected entity, entire data is retrieved irrespective of the value provided for 'Retrieve All Data'.

Inputs:

  • Department - Retrieves the department data from Workday.
  • Location - Retrieves the location data from Workday.
  • Job Profile - Retrieves the job profile data from Workday.
  • Worker Profile - Retrieves the worker profile data from Workday.
  • Effective Worker Profile - Retrieves the Effective Worker Profiles data from Workday.
  • Future Worker Profile - Retrieves the Future Worker Profiles data from Workday.
  • Employment Data - Retrieves the Employment data from Workday.
  • Retrieve All Data - Retrieves entire data for the selected entities.

To use this subflow, Workday Spoke must be installed and corresponding Workday Connection and Credential must be created.
